We have loosened the requirements on our Ring bounty [https://fulu-foundati=
on.ghost.io/r/254317c7?m=3Db503a08a-c4e6-4bfd-bc68-f98315f6032b]. If you ha=
ve the skills and desire to show that security camera owners could control =
their footage=E2=80=94and want to collect $23,580=E2=80=94read on.

Our bounty system, first and foremost, is aimed at drawing attention to wha=
t would be possible if we unlocked our technology. If we are successful in =
passing commonsense reforms to Sec. 1201 of the Digital Millennium Copyrigh=
t Act, we can unleash innovation in the repair tool market and make our dev=
ices work for us.

We believe that this kind of outcome should be accessible to both the techn=
ically-inclined and the average consumer. That is why, in our original crit=
eria, we specified that a winning solution could not modify the original ha=
rdware. As I told WIRED [https://fulu-foundation.ghost.io/r/ec5ad964?m=3Db5=
03a08a-c4e6-4bfd-bc68-f98315f6032b], =E2=80=9CThis needs to be a weekend pr=
oject where someone who was creeped out by a commercial and wants to take b=
ack control can take care of it, get it done, and be able to sleep soundly =
at night knowing that they're the only ones who can see their footage.=E2=
=80=9D

In our effort to make it accessible, we made it too difficult to solve. We =
have attempted to remedy that situation by updating the bounty criteria. No=
w, a winning solution can involve the replacement or addition of up to two =
circuit-board components. We=E2=80=99ve kept the requirement that the modif=
ication process should be carried out in one hour or less to strike the bal=
ance.

Tl;dr =E2=80=93 we want to pay out this bounty, so we=E2=80=99ve made adjus=
tments to make it possible. To submit your solution, double check that you=
=E2=80=99ve met all the criteria [https://fulu-foundation.ghost.io/r/867cf9=
fd?m=3Db503a08a-c4e6-4bfd-bc68-f98315f6032b] and then contact the FULU boun=
ty team at bounty@fulu.org.



















